text: The brown-spotted moray (Gymnothorax fuscomaculatus) is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian Oceans.Gymnothorax fuscomaculatus at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Schultz in 1953 and is also commonly known as the freckled moray.Gymnothorax fuscomaculatus at www.fishbase.org. ==References== ==External links== * Fishes of Australia : Gymnothorax fuscomaculatus brown-spotted moray Category:Marine fish of Northern Australia brown-spotted moray
